HEADWORD: Hippodrome
<hw>Hip"po*drome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>hippodromos</ets>, Gr. <?/; <grk>"i`ppos</grk> horse + <?/ course,
fr. <?/ to run: cf. F. <ets>hippodrome</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Gr. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A place set apart for equestrian and
chariot races.</def>⟦br⟧
